Hold on now. She brings up some good point too. Like I said in my response back to her, who is removing time from their recordings? This may have been a subject that was touched upon so maybe I missed it, but it is a subject that can affect the validity of messages received and posted. If time or in this case audio is removed from the recording because it is noted by the researcher to be silence or just noise, who is to say that someone else doesn&#39;t hear something in those &quot;dead&quot; spaces. We all know that most files can be heard differently by most people who listen to them.

In my opinion this is a major issue.

Regards,

Frank R.

